Looking at the code I read earlier, in the `startGame` function around line 306-318, there's already logic for this:

```javascript
function startGame(level = 1) {
    game.level = level;
    game.won = false;
    game.moves = 0;
    game.visited.clear();

    // Calculate maze size based on level
    const size = Math.min(
        CONFIG.baseSize + (level - 1) * CONFIG.sizeIncrement,
        CONFIG.maxSize
    );
    game.width = size;
    game.height = size;
```

